FBIS3-22806 "jptnd006___94069" JPRS-TND-94-006 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:PROLIFERATION ISSUES 4 March 1994 INTERNATIONAL Reporting on IAEA Inspection of DPRK Nuclear Facilities Yongbyon Nuclear Facilities Inspected SK0403051794 Seoul CHUNGANG ILBO in Korean 4 Mar 94 p 1 SK0403051794 Seoul CHUNGANG ILBO Language: Korean Article Type:BFN [Report by Yu Chae-sik from Vienna] [Text] Hans Meyer, a spokesman of the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA], said on 3 March that the UN nuclear inspection team conducted the first inspection of North Korea's nuclear facilities in a year. He said: "The UN inspection team inspected nuclear facilities in Yongbyon, North Korea for the first time. After the inspection, the inspection team returned to the state guest house and reported this to the IAEA over the telephone." Avoiding mentioning the details of the nuclear inspection, Meyer said: As I understand it, the six-member inspection team did not face any obstacle [ottohan changae-edo chikmyonhaji anun kosuro algo itta] in the course of the inspection of the nuclear facilities in North Korea.
